	<Title>
		Ordering fast food? Portion size counts
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;You can eat healthy away from home, even at fast-food restaurants. If you&apos;re ordering fast food, skip burgers with two or three beef patties, which can pack more than 1,000 calories and 70 grams of fat. Instead, choose a regular- or children&apos;s-sized hamburger, which has about 250 to 300 calories. Also, skip the large serving of french fries or onion rings and ask for a small serving instead. This switch alone saves 200 to 300 calories.&lt;/p&gt;
	</Body>
